<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="405" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1148,2039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1148,1174]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Yellowish species with unpatterned wing (
<figureCitation box="[780,875,1148,1174]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1838,1862]" captionTargetBox="[170,1425,188,1794]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1435,181,1814]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Dasymallomyia ditenostyla Alexander, 1964: A, habitus (male); B, mesonotum; C, wing; D, male terminalia, dorsal view; E, ibid, lateral view; F, gonocoxite and gonostyli, ventral view; G, ibid, lateral view (left = dorsal); H, aedeagal complex, dorsal view; I, ibid, lateral view (left = dorsal). Scale bars: A, C, 2 mm; B, 0.5 mm; D–H, 0.1 mm.Arrow shows small tooth on clasper of gonostylus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902790" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902790/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Presutural area of mesonotum and scutal lobe polished, with one black stripe and two pairs of black spots on prescutum, and with two large dark spots on scutal lobe. Legs yellow with narrow brown ring at distal 1/6 of each femur. Halter pale yellow. Abdomen mainly brown. Clasper of gonostylus thin, blade-shaped, rounded at tip, outer margin with small point near middle. Lobe of gonostylus black, distinctly bifid; anterior branch about as long as posterior branch, rounded on distal part in lateral view; posterior branch strongly widened, single-pointed on posteroventral corner.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
