<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1149]" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">
<emphasis box="[199,313,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Brown on tergites and yellow on sternites, densely covered with long yellow setae; anterior part of tergite 1 yellowish; caudal margins of tergites weakly yellowish. Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[1138,1264,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1838,1862]" captionTargetBox="[170,1425,188,1794]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1435,181,1814]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Dasymallomyia ditenostyla Alexander, 1964: A, habitus (male); B, mesonotum; C, wing; D, male terminalia, dorsal view; E, ibid, lateral view; F, gonocoxite and gonostyli, ventral view; G, ibid, lateral view (left = dorsal); H, aedeagal complex, dorsal view; I, ibid, lateral view (left = dorsal). Scale bars: A, C, 2 mm; B, 0.5 mm; D–H, 0.1 mm.Arrow shows small tooth on clasper of gonostylus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902790" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902790/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">Figs 3D–E</figureCitation>
) with tergite 9 produced posteriorly at middle of caudal margin. Sternite 9 strongly produced ventrally at center. Gonocoxite longer than tergite 9, broad on basal part, rounded at tip. Clasper of gonostylus (
<figureCitation box="[993,1117,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1838,1862]" captionTargetBox="[170,1425,188,1794]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1435,181,1814]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Dasymallomyia ditenostyla Alexander, 1964: A, habitus (male); B, mesonotum; C, wing; D, male terminalia, dorsal view; E, ibid, lateral view; F, gonocoxite and gonostyli, ventral view; G, ibid, lateral view (left = dorsal); H, aedeagal complex, dorsal view; I, ibid, lateral view (left = dorsal). Scale bars: A, C, 2 mm; B, 0.5 mm; D–H, 0.1 mm.Arrow shows small tooth on clasper of gonostylus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902790" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902790/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">Figs 3F–G</figureCitation>
) subhyaline, thin, about 1.5 times as long as lobe of gonostylus, wide on basal part, rounded at tip; outer margin with small point at middle. Lobe of gonostylus black, distinctly bifid; anterior branch about as long as posterior branch, rounded on distal part in lateral view, curled outward at tip; posterior branch strongly widened and bilobed on distal 1/4, pointed at each tip; small setose lobe present between anterior and posterior branches. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1068,1183,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1838,1862]" captionTargetBox="[170,1425,188,1794]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1435,181,1814]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Dasymallomyia ditenostyla Alexander, 1964: A, habitus (male); B, mesonotum; C, wing; D, male terminalia, dorsal view; E, ibid, lateral view; F, gonocoxite and gonostyli, ventral view; G, ibid, lateral view (left = dorsal); H, aedeagal complex, dorsal view; I, ibid, lateral view (left = dorsal). Scale bars: A, C, 2 mm; B, 0.5 mm; D–H, 0.1 mm.Arrow shows small tooth on clasper of gonostylus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902790" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902790/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">Figs 3H–I</figureCitation>
) conical flask-shaped; distal part stout rod-shaped, with claw-shaped lobe at tip; dorsal surface near tip with membranous region; tip directed posteroventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1149]" box="[199,1115,1014,1041]" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,1015,1041]" pageId="6" pageNumber="407">Measurements.</emphasis>
Male (n = 3): body length 
<quantity box="[684,821,1014,1041]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.75" metricValueMax="6.2" metricValueMin="5.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="407" unit="mm" value="5.75" valueMax="6.2" valueMin="5.3">5.3–6.2 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[973,1111,1015,1041]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.7" metricValueMax="7.2" metricValueMin="6.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="407" unit="mm" value="6.7" valueMax="7.2" valueMin="6.2">6.2–7.2 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
